@node "Intro" "Introduction"
Well, @{fg shine}JinxChoice@{fg text} was programmed to ease the handle with emulators. Today there are many patches executed in the startup-sequence, many prefsfiles copied into ram:env. These things take memory and processorcycles.

In fact you might say "hey there are many of startup-selectors available". Thats right but no one of them satisfied me. I wanted to create a nice looking and configurable selector.

JinxChoice will open a nice requester which lets you choose what kind of system (@{fg fill}Macintosh , PC or Workbench@{fg text}) you want to boot.

It will be inserted very early in your startup-sequence so that all that useless Patches and Assign won´t be executed.
@endnode

