@node "Install" "Installation"
 The easiest way to install JinxChoice is to use the wonderful installerscript.

If you don`t trust the installer you have to do the following:

 · copy JinxChoice where ever you want (C: recommented)
 · copy the two scripts JC-startup and JC-clearseq to S:
 · add the following lines at the top of S:startup-sequence
 · copy C:mousetest to C:

;---JinxChoice start ---------------------------------------------

execute S:JC-startup

C:JinxChoice [M=Macstartup] [P=PCstartup] [E=Prepemul] [S=Screenmode] [AUTO]

execute S:JC-clearseq

;---Here beginns your standard startup-sequence --------------------



You should also have/make 2 short startups for your mac/pc-emulator which contain assigns and specific patches.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Syntax"
To activate JinxChoice on startup you only have to hold the left mouse button until the screen opens. There you can choose the desired item either by hitting the cross with the mouse pointer or by using the cursor up/down keys.

@{u}The CLI Usage of JinxChoice is:@{uu}

M=MAC/K,P=PC/K,E=EMUL/K,S=SCREEN/K,H=HOTKEY,AUTO/S

@{u}Explanation of options:@{uu}

@{b}MAC@{ub} Should contain the name of an batchfile (i.e. mac-startup) which executes your MAC-Emulator

@{b}PC@{ub} Should contain the name of an batchfile (i.e. pc-startup) which executes your PC_Emulator

@{b}EMUL@{ub} Enter here the program which prepares your Mac-Emulation.


@{b}AUTO@{ub} If this switch is set and the button `PrepEmul` was chosen the first time the computer was turned on JinxChoice will automatically execute the `mac-sequence` after the following Reset (the JinxChoice screen won`t appear). Otherwise (when the switch isn`t set) the normal `startup-sequence` will be executed. Note for AFS-User: This switch doesn`t work, if your bootpartition is AFS-formated.

@{b}SCREEN@{ub} Available parameters are:

Here you can enter the screen mode in hex code BUT without the ->$<- character.

Example: S=39024 for Multiscan screenmode

If SCREEN is not chosen JinxChoice will appear on an normal HiRes screen.


AUTO If this switch is set and the button `PrepEmul` was chosen the first time the computer was turned on JinxChoice will automatically execute the `mac-sequence` after the following Reset (the JinxChoice screen won`t appear). Otherwise (when the switch isn`t set) the normal `startup-sequence` will be executed. Note for AFS-User: This switch doesn`t work, if your bootpartition is AFS-formated.

@{u}Examples:@{uu}

C:JinxChoice M=S:mac-startup E=C:rsrv-cold S=39024

an mac-only requester on a Multiscan screen will be opened after pressing LMB while booting


@{u}                                                                      @{uu}     

C:JinxChoice P=S:pc-startup S=40D20001

an peecee requester will be opened on a CGfx-screen (640*480) after pressing LMB while booting.
@endnode

@node "require" "Requirements"
 @{u}System Requirements@{uu}

All you need is an Amiga with AmigaOS 2.1+ ! That isn`t too much I think.
@endnode

